SOP – Replace Identity.API Artifacts with New ZIP
1️⃣ Go to the repository folder

Navigate to your project directory.

cd <your-repository-folder>

Example:

cd ~/alfpro
2️⃣ Navigate to the artifacts folder
cd publish-artifacts

Check contents:

ls

You should see:

ApiGateway
Employee.API
Identity.API
Leave.API
Payroll.API
3️⃣ Delete existing Identity.API files

⚠️ Only remove files inside the folder, not the folder itself.

rm -rf Identity.API/*

Verify:

ls Identity.API

It should return empty.

4️⃣ Copy the new ZIP file into the folder

Example if your zip is called:

Identity.API_Release.zip

Copy it:

cp ~/Downloads/Identity.API_Release.zip Identity.API/

Check:

ls Identity.API

Expected:

Identity.API_Release.zip
5️⃣ Unzip the new build

Go inside the folder:

cd Identity.API

Unzip:

unzip Identity.API_Release.zip

Now you should see:

Identity.API.dll
Identity.API.runtimeconfig.json
appsettings.json
dependencies...
6️⃣ Remove the ZIP file (optional but recommended)
rm Identity.API_Release.zip

Verify:

ls

You should only see artifact files.

7️⃣ Go back to repository root
cd ../../

Confirm Git sees changes:

git status

You should see many modified files under:

publish-artifacts/Identity.API
8️⃣ Commit the changes
git add publish-artifacts/Identity.API

Then commit:

git commit -m "Updated Identity.API artifacts"
9️⃣ Push to GitHub
git push
🔟 CI/CD will deploy automatically

Once pushed:

Git Push
   ↓
Jenkins Pipeline Triggered
   ↓
Files copied to /opt/alfpro/Identity.API
   ↓
systemctl restart identity-api
   ↓
New Identity API running
✔ Verify deployment on server

SSH into server:

ls /opt/alfpro/Identity.API

Check service:

systemctl status identity-api

Expected:

Active: active (running)
